the darkness, pine trees and hills rushing up to the train—what a noise these boys were making. Won’t they ever stop dancing? Yes, amazingly simple—at times there was something like genius in the workings of fate—

“All right, I shall go and lie down a bit,” said Podtyagin dully, and with a heavy sigh started to leave.

“Where is the grand fellow going? Stop—stay a bit longer,” Alfyorov muttered gaily.

